<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0e673939-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9581"><num value="9581">§ 9581.</num><heading> Rulemaking</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s1232/d">section 1232(d) of this title</ref>, the exemption for public property, loans, grants, and benefits in <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s553/a/2">section 553(a)(2) of title 5</ref> shall apply to the Institute.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0e67393a-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/279/tI/s191">Pub. L. 107–279, title I, § 191</ref>, <date date="2002-11-05">Nov. 5, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1974">116 Stat. 1974</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
